
  The file pystrf.f* contains modified routine PYSTRF for * version of Pythia,
 and some auxiliary routines.   

  HELIX string model steering parameters [modified helix scenario as described in
 arXiv:1101.2407 ]

  MSTU(199) = 0    no helix ( standard fragmentation )
              1    reserved
              2    modified helix ( with constant pitch )
              3    modified helix for light quarks only ( makes sense in Z0 decay only ) 

  PARJ(102)        helix radius  ( replacing PARJ(21), numerically very close )
  PARJ(103)        sigma of helix radius
  PARJ(104)        S parameter [rad/GeV] 
  PARJ(109)        tolerance ( num.precision )

  Subroutine PYPTSCM(..)  generates pt according to modified helix parametrization

  other functions/routines: subroutine define_winding(..)
                            function helix(..)  